(firstQuint)Umbilical Cord Mesenchymal Stem Cell Transplantation for Lupus Nephritis.

 Systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) is a multisystem autoimmune disease.

 Lupus nephritis (LN) is one of the most serious complications of SLE.

 The current clinical treatments of LN mainly include steroids and immunosuppressive drugs, but drug side effects are obvious.

